capabilities, it was a textbook Vertical Integrator [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/cabbe5f6-a560-4574-b74b-d48421812a44?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]:=C2=A0
Integrate multiple cutting-edge-but-proven technologies.
Develop significant in-house capabilities across their stack.
Modularize commoditized components while controlling overall system integra=
tion.
Compete directly with incumbents.
Offer products that are better, faster, or cheaper (often all three).
Peter Thiel argued [ https://substack.com/redirect/2bb8bc26-34c5-46eb-8197-=
72a6e05256be?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU ] that there were only two ways to make money coming up with new thing=
s: software and =E2=80=9Ccomplex, vertically integrated monopolies.=E2=80=
=9D=C2=A0
While most modern founders and investors remain tied to the lessons learned=
 over the past half-century of software development, if I=E2=80=99m right, =
they should be studying people like Rockefeller, Ford, and Edison to prepar=
e for what=E2=80=99s coming. The farther backward you can look, the farther=
 forward you are likely to see.
Edison faced many of the challenges we discussed in Part III [ https://subs=
tack.com/redirect/b3473aad-c535-40ae-8c3b-4e6de4d760f3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] that modern Vertical Integ=
rators face today:=C2=A0
It requires building at least two companies.=C2=A0
Hardware by itself is just really hard.=C2=A0
Incumbents are good at what they do and have advantages.=C2=A0
Figuring out the right level of integration is not obvious.=C2=A0
You can=E2=80=99t pivot nearly as easily.=C2=A0
Something better might come along.=C2=A0
Getting to revenue takes a lot of money.
I won=E2=80=99t spell them all out here, but if you=E2=80=99d like, read ba=
ck the story above and see if you can find examples of each. Even Edison=E2=
=80=99s pivot to AC, which looks smooth in hindsight, required merging with=
 Thomson-Houston, which was further along in AC. =E2=80=9CPlus =C3=A7a chan=
ge,=E2=80=9D as someone at Edison=E2=80=99s Compagnie Continentale, where a=
 young Nikola Tesla would get his start, might have said.=C2=A0=C2=A0
But as I wrote in Part II [ https://substack.com/redirect/65e857cb-a917-422=
f-a28a-531cd126e085?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU ], =E2=80=9CIf the Vertical Integrator can pull all of that off=
