or: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">argued</a><span> that the=
re were only two ways to make money coming up with new things: software and=
 &#8220;complex, vertically integrated monopolies.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">While most modern founders and investors remain tied to th=
e lessons learned over the past half-century of software development, if I&=
#8217;m right, they should be studying people like Rockefeller, Ford, and E=
dison to prepare for what&#8217;s coming. The farther backward you can look=
, the farther forward you are likely to see.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, =
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Edi=
son faced many of the challenges we discussed in </span><a href=3D"https://=
